                    </div>
                    <span>Being one of this book's reviewers I can say that Ravi successfully introduces a subject - IP Routing - which can easily eat up hundreds and hundreds of pages in only 300 pages, without sacrificing content and quality. Its page count is this books advantage, so if you are looking for an O'Reilly-style introduction to IP Routing, get this book.<P>Edgar Danielyan<BR>Danielyan Consulting<BR>www.danielyan.com</span>
                  
